                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4698: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-24T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 24, 1931—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>236. For Gibson. Reference is made to your telegram No. 264 of July 24, 10 a.m.
                    We understand your point of view and agree with your plan. However, since all
                    information and material relating to some of the matters which will be dealt
                    with by the Committee of Experts have been concentrated in your hands, the Near
                    Eastern debt settlement, for example, and since General Dawes probably will not
                    have followed these angles of the question nearly as closely, you will naturally
                    want to delay your departure until he feels certain about all the important
                    matters that will come before the Committee.</p>
                <p>I do not want to make this message final until I can talk with the President on
                    Monday. He has gone away for the week-end and it was his idea that you go to
                    London. However, I am certain that he will agree.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
